  "worklog": "## 2026-03-29 23:08 UTC \u2014 Pillar 1: Copy Intelligence \u2014 SELL Signal Fix\n\n**Task:** Investigate signal count discrepancy between integrator (11 signals) and raw data (50 signals).\n\n**Root cause:** Integrator only counted BUY side signals, completely ignoring 39 SELL signals. SELL Up = bearish (dumping up tokens), SELL Down = bullish. This is critical directional information that was being discarded.\n\n**Fix:** Added SELL-side counting \u2014 SELL Up/Yes increments down_count, SELL Down/No increments up_count. Now reads all 50 signals.\n\n**Before fix:** bearish@100% confidence (based on 11/50 signals \u2014 overconfident)\n**After fix:** bearish@68% confidence (based on 50/50 signals \u2014 properly calibrated)\n\n**Impact:** The copy conviction boost fires at confidence >= 100. With properly calibrated confidence, it will be much more selective \u2014 only boosting when there's overwhelming consensus, not just when we're reading a tiny sample. This prevents false conviction boosts.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-29 22:42 UTC \u2014 Pillar 3: End-of-Day Report\n\n**Task:** Write comprehensive daily P&L report for Sunday March 29.\n\n**Summary:** 1 trade, 1 win, +$10.36. Total capital $1,321.36. But Sunday was a BUILD day \u2014 4 strategy deployments, 2 bug fixes, W14 projection showing 82% WR / $53/day potential. W13 closed at +$216.35 (101 trades, 55% WR). V3.1+V3.2+V3.3 should transform W14.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-29 22:08 UTC \u2014 Pillar 2: Edge Development \u2014 Sub-Hour Timing Analysis\n\n**Task:** Find sub-hour sweet spots within V3 active hours using 40 weekday YES trades.\n\n**Key Findings:**\n\n1. **First 30 min beats second 30 min:** 86% WR (18W/3L) vs 79% (15W/4L). The edge degrades as the hour progresses.\n\n2. **Hour 12h is the gold mine:** 14W/2L (88% WR) across the full hour. Only weakness: :20-29 bucket (1W/2L, 33%). All other 10-min buckets are 100% WR.\n\n3. **Hour 19h degrades after :30:** First 30 min = 6W/0L (100%). After :30 = 3W/3L (50%). The signal quality drops sharply mid-hour.\n\n4. **V4 idea: Half-hour filter for 19h and 20h.** Only trade 19:00-19:29 (100% WR) and skip 19:30-19:59 (50% WR). For 20h, 20:00-20:19 shows 4W/1L (80%). Small sample but consistent pattern.\n\n5. **12h:20-29 is an anomaly:** Only 33% WR in an otherwise perfect hour. Could be 5-min market reset timing.\n\n**Action:** Log this as V4 candidate. Need 20+ more trades to validate half-hour patterns before implementing.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-29 21:38 UTC \u2014 Pillar 1: Copy Intelligence \u2014 Bot Farm Filter\n\n**Task:** Quantify and filter bot farm contamination in copy signal data.\n\n**Finding:** **90% of top wallets (18/20) are bot farm accounts** \u2014 all with exactly 30 trades in 1 market at $0.94+ avg price. Only 2 legit wallets remain: Considerate-Racer (150 trades, 2 markets, $11k vol) and Dental-Latex (60 trades, 1 market, $1.2k vol).\n\n**Fix:** Added bot farm filter to copy-signal-integrator.py \u2014 skips wallets matching (30 trades + 1 market + avg_price > 0.90). This only affects the fallback path when no recent signals exist, but prevents s",
